{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox website | logo = File:Doodle Logo.svg | screenshot = File:Doodle.com homepage.png | collapsible = yes | collapsetext = Screenshot | caption = | url = {{URL|http://doodle.com/}} | commercial = | type = | registration = Not required | language = 26 languages including: [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[American English]], [[British English]], [[German language|German]], [[French language|French]] and [[Italian language|Italian]] | programming language = [[Javascript]] (through [[JavaServer Faces|JSF]])<ref>https://en.blog.doodle.com/2014/09/29/ever-wondered-how-doodle-works/</ref> | owner = | author = | revenue = | alexa = {{increase}} 1,133 ({{as of|2016|12|1|alt=December 2016}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/Doodle.com |title= Doodle.com Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2016-12-01 }}</ref><!--Updated monthly by OKBot.--> | footnotes = | name = Doodle | logocaption = | content license = | launch date = | current status = Active }}
'''Doodle''' is an online calendar tool for [[time management]], and coordinating [[meeting]]s. It is based in [[Zurich, Switzerland]] and has been operational since 2007. It has offices in [[Berlin]], [[Tel Aviv]], and [[Belgrade]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newlyswissed.com/doodle-scheduling-tool/|title=We've met the people behind the Doodle scheduling tool|date=2018-02-16|work=Newly Swissed – Switzerland Expat Online Magazine|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en-US}}</ref>
Users are asked to determine the best time and date to meet.<ref name="five hours">{{cite book|title=SuperCompetent: The Six Keys to Perform at Your Productive Best|year=2010|publisher=John Wiley and Sons|isbn=978-0-470-59915-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NvLxpdSan5UC&dq=%22Doodle.com%22&source=gbs_navlinks_s|author=Laura Stack|accessdate=31 March 2011|page=79|chapter=SuperCompetent Key 2:availability}}</ref> The organizer then chooses the time that suits everyone and the meeting is booked in your calendar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newlyswissed.com/doodle-scheduling-tool/|title=We've met the people behind the Doodle scheduling tool|date=2018-02-16|work=Newly Swissed – Switzerland Expat Online Magazine|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en-US}}</ref> Meeting coordinators (administrators) receive e-mail alerts for votes and comments. Registration is required to have this function.<ref name="Website of the week">{{cite news|title=Web site of the week: Doodle|url=http://www.kansascity.com/2011/04/07/2782700/web-site-of-the-week-doodle.html|accessdate=12 April 2011|newspaper=[[McClatchy-Tribune News Service]]|date=7 April 2011|author=Eric Goodwin}}</ref>
In 2014 Swiss media giant [[Tamedia]] increased its share in Doodle to 100 percent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tamedia.ch/en/group/newsroom/media-releases/tamedia-completes-acquisition-of-doodle-and-shifts-gears-for-further-investment|title=Newsroom – Tamedia|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en}}</ref> Doodle released its [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] apps in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thenextweb.com/insider/2014/01/07/simple-scheduler-app-doodle-acquired-swiss-media-group-tamedia/|title=Doodle to be Acquired by Tamedia|last=Sawers|first=Paul|date=2014-01-07|work=The Next Web|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en-US}}</ref> They also passed the 20 million monthly user benchmark.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://en.blog.doodle.com/2014/01/29/doodle-crosses-the-20m-user-mark/|title=Doodle crosses the 20M user mark|date=2014-01-29|work=Doodle Blog|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en-US}}</ref>
Doodle acquired [https://meekan.com/ Meekan] in 2016. Meekan is a [[chatbot]] developed in [[Israel]]. Meekan uses [[artificial intelligence]] and [[natural language processing]] to schedule meetings. Doodle has since begun to integrate this technology into their products.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/06/30/doodle-acquires-chatbot-meekan-and-will-integrate-its-a-i-scheduling-assistant/|title=Doodle acquires chatbot Meekan to integrate its A.I. scheduling assistant|date=2016-06-30|work=VentureBeat|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en-US}}</ref>
In 2016, Doodle was used by over 180 million unique users in 175 different countries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenational.ae/business/review-doodle-scheduling-app-gets-straight-to-the-point-1.203109|title=Review: Doodle scheduling app gets straight to the point|work=The National|access-date=2018-08-01|language=en}}</ref>
Doodle interacts with various external calendar systems. [[Google Calendar]], [[Yahoo Calendar]], [[Microsoft Outlook]] and [[Apple iCal]] can be utilized with Doodle to track dates. [[Google Maps]] may also be used to share the location of the event.<ref name="Website of the week" />
Similar popular competing products, which may collectively be designated as "date matchers", include Dudle<ref name="Dudle Information">{{cite web|title=Dudle Homepage|url=http://www.primelife.eu/results/opensource/63-dudle|accessdate=9 July 2011}}</ref> ([[Free Software]] maintained by the [[Dresden University of Technology|TU Dresden]]),<ref name="Privacy enhanced Dudle">{{cite web|title=Privacy enhanced Dudle|url=https://dudle.inf.tu-dresden.de/privacy/|accessdate=9 July 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110122160449/http://dudle.inf.tu-dresden.de/privacy/|archivedate=22 January 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[ScheduleOnce]], [[Tungle]] (which ceased 3 December 2012), [[TimeBridge]] (ceased), [[WhenIsGood]], [[Framadate]],<ref name="Framadate Open Source Date Finder from Famasoft / France">{{cite web|title=Framadate Portal|url=https://framadate.org/|accessdate=8 December 2014}}</ref> [[Xoyondo]],<ref name="Xoyondo - Meeting Scheduler">{{cite web|title=Xoyondo Homepage|url=https://xoyondo.com/|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref> or [[LetsMeetOn]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://letsmeeton.com/|title=LetsMeetOn Website|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref>
