[[File:2009 Oscar party.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Elton John]] and Christopher McDaniel at the 2009 Oscar party]]
The '''Elton John AIDS Foundation Academy Award Party''' is one of the annual parties held in Los Angeles following the [[Academy Award]]s ceremony the same evening. The first party was held in February 1993 at Maple Drive Restaurant and raised $300,000.<ref name="ejaf">{{cite web|url=http://www.ejaf.org/pages/about/fundraising.html|title=About|publisher=Elton John AIDS Foundation|accessdate=28 February 2011}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It had been produced by Patrick Lippert, an AIDS activist who died of the disease just months later.<ref name="BernardinStanton1996">{{cite book |last1=Bernardin |first1=Claude |last2=Stanton |first2=Tom |title=Rocket Man: Elton John from A–Z |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eJGcZSyBflwC&pg=PA73 |accessdate=28 February 2011 |date=January 1996 |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |isbn=978-0-275-95698-1|pages=73–4}}</ref> In recent years it has been held at the [[Pacific Design Center]] and was attended by 650 people in 2009.<ref name="Tele09">{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/oscars/4785204/Oscars-2009-Elton-John-holds-star-studded-party.html|title=Elton John holds star studded party |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=28 February 2011|location=London|date=23 February 2009}}</ref> It is hosted by [[Elton John]] and the [[Elton John AIDS Foundation|AIDS Foundation]], and is one of the most high-profile parties in the Hollywood film industry, particularly for people of British origin working in Hollywood films or the entertainment industry. The annual party contributes to the foundation fund by its high priced ticket sales which are given by invitation only ($3500 or £2400 as of 2009<ref name="Tele09"/>) and a celebrity auction. The 2010 party raised over $8 million or £4 million.<ref>{{cite news |first=Danielle |last=Lawler |author2=Clemmie Moodie |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/celebs/news/2010/03/09/elton-john-oscars-party-raises-4million-115875-22096284/ |title=Elton John Oscars party raises £4million |work=[[Daily Mirror]] |date=9 March 2010|accessdate=28 February 2011}}</ref>
==Venues== *1993 [[65th Academy Awards]]: Maple Drive Restaurant<ref name="Communications2005">{{cite journal |title=In 'n' Out |work=Los Angeles Magazine |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Rl8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA168 |accessdate=28 February 2011|date=September 2005 |publisher=Emmis Communications |page=168 |issn=1522-9149}}</ref> *1994 [[66th Academy Awards]]: *1995 [[67th Academy Awards]]: [[Four Seasons Hotel]], [[Beverly Hills]]<ref name="Cameron-WilsonSpeed1996">{{cite book|last1=Cameron-Wilson|first1=James|last2=Speed|first2=F. Maurice|title=Film Review 1995–6: Including Video Releases|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-apP83xZMBEC|accessdate=28 February 2011|date=January 1996|publisher=Virgin Books|isbn=978-0-86369-928-3}}</ref> *1996 [[68th Academy Awards]]: *1997 [[69th Academy Awards]]: *1998 [[70th Academy Awards]]: [[Spago]] restaurant, [[Beverly Hills]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seeing-stars.com/dine2/Spago.shtml|title=Spago|publisher=Seeing Stars|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref> *1999 [[71st Academy Awards]]: Pagani<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/mar/15/news/cl-17399 |title=Vanity Fair Takes Oscar Party Lead |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=March 15, 1999|accessdate=28 February 2011|first=Irene|last=Lacher}}</ref> *2000 [[72nd Academy Awards]]: *2001 [[73rd Academy Awards]]: Moomba restaurant, [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cdnedge.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/1218425.stm |title=Webcasts from LA |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=March 25, 2001|accessdate=28 February 2011}}</ref> *2002 [[74th Academy Awards]]: Moomba restaurant, [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.cnn.com/2002-03-26/entertainment/in.hop.oscars_1_oscar-gold-silent-auction-gourmet-dinner?_s=PM:SHOWBIZ |title=Oscar 2002 after parties |publisher=[[CNN]] |date=26 March 2002 |accessdate=28 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101026095200/http://articles.cnn.com/2002-03-26/entertainment/in.hop.oscars_1_oscar-gold-silent-auction-gourmet-dinner?_s=PM%3ASHOWBIZ |archivedate=26 October 2010 |df= }}</ref> *2003 [[75th Academy Awards]]: *2004 [[76th Academy Awards]]: *2005 [[77th Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]] *2006 [[78th Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]] *2007 [[79th Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]]<ref name="The Hollywood reporter">{{cite news |title=? |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5lUIAQAAMAAJ |accessdate=28 February 2011 |year=2007 |page=220 |publisher=Wilkerson Daily Corp.}}</ref> *2008 [[80th Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]] *2009 [[81st Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]]<ref name="Tele09"/> *2010 [[82nd Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.okmagazine.com/2010/03/sir-elton-johns-oscar-viewing-party-brings-out-a-variety-of-stars/ |title=Sir Elton John’s Oscar Viewing Party Brings Out a Variety of Stars |work=[[OK Magazine]] |date=March 8, 2010 |accessdate=28 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110403033214/http://www.okmagazine.com/2010/03/sir-elton-johns-oscar-viewing-party-brings-out-a-variety-of-stars/ |archivedate=3 April 2011 |df= }}</ref> *2011 [[83rd Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1361348/OSCARS-2011-Kim-Kardashian-Elton-John-schmooze-star-studded-party.html |title=Can you feel the love tonight? Kim Kardashian schmoozes with Elton John at his star-studded Oscars party |work=[[Daily Mail]] |date=28 February 2011|accessdate=28 February 2011|location=London}}</ref> *2012 [[84th Academy Awards]]: West Hollywood Park, [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2012/02/elton-john-oscar-party-miley-cyrus-kim-kardashian-2012.html|title=Elton John's Oscar party turns 20 with Klum, Kardashian, the kid|publisher=''[[Los Angeles Times]]''|accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref> *2013 [[85th Academy Awards]]: [[Pacific Design Center]], [[West Hollywood]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gossipcop.com/elton-john-oscar-viewing-party-pics-photos-academy-awards-pictures-aids-foundation/#0|title=Elton John Oscar Viewing Party Photos - Academy Award Aids Foundation|publisher=Gossip Cop Media|accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref>
