==Events== * [[705]] &ndash; Empress [[Wu Zetian]] abdicates the throne, restoring the [[Tang dynasty]]. *[[1316]] &ndash; [[Battle of Picotin]] between [[Ferdinand of Majorca]] and the forces of [[Matilda of Hainaut]] *[[1371]] &ndash; [[Robert II of Scotland|Robert II]] becomes King of [[Kingdom of Scotland|Scotland]], beginning the [[House of Stuart|Stuart]] dynasty. *[[1495]] &ndash; King [[Charles VIII of France]] enters [[Naples]] to claim the city's throne. *[[1632]] &ndash; [[Galileo Galilei|Galileo]]'s ''[[Dialogue Concerning the Two Chief World Systems]]'' is published. *[[1651]] &ndash; [[St. Peter's Flood]]: A storm surge floods the [[German Bight|Frisian coast]], drowning 15,000 people. *[[1744]] &ndash; [[War of the Austrian Succession]]: The [[Battle of Toulon (1744)|Battle of Toulon]] causes several [[Royal Navy]] captains to be [[court-martial]]ed, and the [[Articles of War]] to be amended. *[[1797]] &ndash; The [[last Invasion of Britain]] begins near [[Fishguard]], [[Wales]]. *[[1819]] &ndash; By the [[Adams–Onís Treaty]], Spain [[History of Florida|sells Florida]] to the United States for five million U.S. dollars. *[[1821]] &ndash; [[Greek War of Independence]]: [[Alexander Ypsilantis]] crosses the [[Prut]] river at [[Sculeni]] into the [[Danubian Principalities]]. *[[1847]] &ndash; [[Mexican–American War]]: The [[Battle of Buena Vista]]: Five thousand American troops defeat 15,000 [[Mexico|Mexicans]] troops. *[[1848]] &ndash; The [[French Revolution of 1848]], which would lead to the establishment of the [[French Second Republic]], begins. *[[1853]] &ndash; [[Washington University in St. Louis]] is founded as Eliot Seminary in [[St. Louis, Missouri]]. *[[1855]] &ndash; The [[Pennsylvania State University]] is founded in [[State College, Pennsylvania]] (as the Farmers' High School of Pennsylvania). *[[1856]] &ndash; The United States [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] opens its first national convention in [[Pittsburgh]]. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[Jefferson Davis]] is officially inaugurated for a six-year term as the [[President of the Confederate States of America]] in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. He was previously inaugurated as a provisional president on February 18, 1861. *[[1872]] &ndash; The [[Prohibition Party]] holds its first national convention in [[Columbus, Ohio]], nominating [[James Black (prohibitionist)|James Black]] as its presidential nominee. *[[1878]] &ndash; In [[Utica, New York]], [[Frank Woolworth]] opens the first of many of five-and-dime [[F. W. Woolworth Company|Woolworth]] stores. *[[1889]] &ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[Grover Cleveland]] [[Enabling Act of 1889|signs a bill]] admitting [[North Dakota]], [[South Dakota]], [[Montana]] and [[Washington (state)|Washington]] as [[U.S. state]]s. *[[1899]] &ndash; [[Philippine Revolutionary Army|Filipino forces]] led by General [[Antonio Luna]] [[Second Battle of Caloocan|launch counterattacks for the first time]] against the American forces during the [[Philippine–American War]]. The Filipinos fail to regain Manila from the Americans. *[[1904]] &ndash; The United Kingdom sells a meteorological station on the [[South Orkney Islands]] to [[Argentina]]; the islands are subsequently claimed by the United Kingdom in 1908. *[[1907]] &ndash; [[Robert Baden-Powell]] made the first scouting camp in [[Brownsea]], England. *[[1909]] &ndash; The sixteen [[battleship]]s of the [[Great White Fleet]], led by {{USS|Connecticut|BB-18|6}}, return to the United States after a voyage around the world. *[[1915]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: The [[Imperial German Navy]] institutes [[unrestricted submarine warfare]]. *[[1921]] &ndash; After Russian forces under Baron [[Roman von Ungern-Sternberg]] drive the Chinese out, the [[Bogd Khan]] is reinstalled as the [[Khagan|emperor]] of [[Mongolia (1911–24)|Mongolia]]. *[[1924]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Calvin Coolidge]] becomes the first President to deliver a [[Radio in the United States|radio address]] from the [[White House]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] orders General [[Douglas MacArthur's escape from the Philippines|Douglas MacArthur out of the Philippines]] as the Japanese victory becomes inevitable. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: Members of the [[White Rose]] resistance, [[Sophie Scholl]], [[Hans Scholl]], and [[Christoph Probst]] are executed in [[Nazi Germany]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; World War II: American aircraft mistakenly bomb the Dutch towns of [[Nijmegen]], [[Arnhem]], [[Enschede]] and [[Deventer]], resulting in 800 dead in Nijmegen alone. * 1944 &ndash; World War II: The Soviet [[Red Army]] recaptures [[Krivoi Rog]]. *[[1946]] &ndash; The "[[X Article|Long Telegram]]", proposing how the United States should deal with the Soviet Union, arrives from the US embassy in Moscow.<ref>{{Cite book|title=The World Transformed:1945 to the Present|last=Hunt|first=Michael|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2013|isbn=9780199371020|location=|pages=44|quote=|via=}}</ref> *[[1957]] &ndash; [[Ngô Đình Diệm]] of [[South Vietnam]] survives a [[Viet Cong|communist]] shooting assassination attempt in [[Buôn Ma Thuột]]. *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Egypt]] and [[Syria]] join to form the [[United Arab Republic]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Lee Petty]] wins the first [[Daytona 500]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; The [[Official Irish Republican Army]] detonates a [[car bomb]] at [[Aldershot]] barracks, killing seven and injuring nineteen others. *[[1973]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: Following President [[Richard Nixon]]'s [[Nixon visit to China 1972|visit]] to the [[China|People's Republic of China]], the two countries agree to establish [[:wikt:liaison|liaison]] offices. *[[1974]] &ndash; The [[Organisation of Islamic Cooperation|Organisation of the Islamic Conference]] summit begins in [[Lahore]], Pakistan. Thirty-seven countries attend and twenty-two heads of state and government participate. It also recognizes [[Bangladesh]]. * 1974 &ndash; [[Samuel Byck]] attempts to hijack an aircraft at [[Baltimore/Washington International Airport]] with the intention of crashing it into the [[White House]] to assassinate [[Richard Nixon]], but is killed by police.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050109073412/http://www.rvv.com/peacemaker/Samuel_Byck.htm The Samuel Byck Assassination Attempt]</ref> *[[1980]] &ndash; [[Miracle on Ice]]: In [[Lake Placid, New York]], the United States hockey team defeats the [[Soviet Union]] hockey team 4–3. *[[1983]] &ndash; The notorious [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] flop ''[[Moose Murders]]'' opens and closes on the same night at the [[Eugene O'Neill Theatre]]. *[[1986]] &ndash; Start of the [[People Power Revolution]] in the [[Philippines]]. *[[1994]] &ndash; [[Aldrich Ames]] and his wife are charged by the [[United States Department of Justice]] with spying for the Soviet Union. *[[1995]] &ndash; The [[Corona (satellite)|Corona]] [[reconnaissance satellite]] program, in existence from 1959 to 1972, is declassified. *[[1997]] &ndash; In [[Roslin, Midlothian]], British scientists announce that an adult sheep named [[Dolly the sheep|Dolly]] has been successfully [[cloning|cloned]]. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[Angola]]n political and rebel leader [[Jonas Savimbi]] is killed in a military ambush. *[[2005]] &ndash; The 6.4 {{M|w}} [[2005 Zarand earthquake|Zarand earthquake]] shakes the [[Kerman Province]] of [[Iran]] with a maximum [[Mercalli intensity scale|Mercalli intensity]] of VIII (''Severe''), leaving 612 people dead and 1,411 injured. *[[2006]] &ndash; At least six men stage Britain's [[Securitas depot robbery|biggest robbery]], stealing £53m (about $92.5 million or €78 million) from a Securitas depot in [[Tonbridge]], [[Kent]]. *[[2011]] &ndash; [[New Zealand]]'s second deadliest [[2011 Christchurch earthquake|earthquake]] strikes [[Christchurch]], killing 185 people. * 2011 &ndash; [[Bahraini uprising (2011–present)|Bahraini uprising]]: Tens of thousands of people [[March of loyalty to martyrs|march in protest]] against the deaths of seven victims killed by police and army forces during previous protests. *[[2012]] &ndash; A [[2012 Buenos Aires rail disaster|train crash]] in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]], kills 51 people and injures 700 others. *[[2014]] &ndash; President [[Viktor Yanukovych]] of [[Ukraine]] is impeached by the [[Verkhovna Rada]] of Ukraine by a vote of 328–0, fulfilling a major goal of the [[Euromaidan]] rebellion. *[[2015]] &ndash; A ferry carrying 100 passengers [[Sinking of the ML Mostofa-3|capsizes]] in the [[Padma River]], killing 70 people. *[[2018]] &ndash; A man throws a grenade at the U.S embassy in [[Podgorica]], [[Montenegro]]. He dies at the scene from a second explosion, with no one else hurt.
