ico]], 21st [[President of Guatemala]] (b. 1878) *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Tom Cole (racing driver)|Tom Cole]], Welsh-American racing driver (b. 1922) *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Salvatore Quasimodo]], Italian novelist and poet, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] Laureate (b. 1901) *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Dündar Taşer]], Turkish soldier and politician (b. 1925) *[[1977]] &ndash; [[Robert Middleton]], American actor (b. 1911) * 1977 &ndash; [[Alan Reed]], American actor, original voice of [[Fred Flintstone]] (b.1907) *[[1979]] &ndash; [[Ahmad Zahir]], Afghan singer-songwriter (b. 1946) *[[1980]] &ndash; [[Charles Miller (musician)|Charles Miller]], American saxophonist and flute player (b. 1939) *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Jorge Luis Borges]], Argentine short-story writer, essayist, poet and translator (b. 1899) * 1986 &ndash; [[Alan Jay Lerner]], American composer and songwriter (b. 1918) *[[1987]] &ndash; [[Stanisław Bareja]], Polish actor, director, and screenwriter (b. 1929) *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Erna Berger]], German soprano and actress (b. 1900) *[[1991]] &ndash; [[Peggy Ashcroft]], English actress (b. 1907) *[[1994]] &ndash; [[Lionel Grigson]], English pianist, composer, and educator (b. 1942) * 1994 &ndash; [[Henry Mancini]], American composer and conductor (b. 1924) * 1994 &ndash; [[Marcel Mouloudji]], French singer and actor (b. 1922) *[[1995]] &ndash; [[Els Aarne]], Ukrainian-Estonian pianist, composer, and educator (b. 1917) * 1995 &ndash; [[Rory Gallagher]], Irish singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer (b. 1949) * 1995 &ndash; [[Roger Zelazny]], American author and poet (b. 1937) *[[1996]] &ndash; [[Noemí Gerstein]], Argentinian sculptor and illustrator (b. 1908) *[[1997]] &ndash; [[Richard Jaeckel]], American actor (b. 1926) *[[1999]] &ndash; [[Bernie Faloney]], American-Canadian football player and sportscaster (b. 1932) *[[2000]] &ndash; [[Attilio Bertolucci]], Italian poet and author (b. 1911) *[[2002]] &ndash; [[June Jordan]], American author and activist (b. 1936) 