{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=July 2011}} {{orphan|date=May 2011}} {{notability|Companies|date=September 2018}} }} {{Infobox company | name = National Career Fairs Inc. | logo = | type = | genre = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{start date|2001}} | founder = | defunct = | location_city = [[Henderson, Nevada]] | location_country = [[United States]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Employment]] | products = Job Fairs | services = | market cap = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 20 | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.nationalcareerfairs.com/ nationalcareerfairs.com] | clothing logo = | caption = Making Connections Face to Face }}
'''National Career Fairs''' is a company founded in 2001 by Scott Lobenberg to produce [[job fair]]s in cities across the United States. The events are a place where job seekers meet face-to-face with employers, educational institutions, and professional [[résumé]] writers.
==Company information== National Career Fairs has its headquarters in [[Henderson, Nevada]], and is under the leadership of Scott Lobenberg, founder and president, and Diana Nicholson, [[CEO]]. The company was incorporated in 2001,<ref>[http://www.allbusiness.com/technology/technology-services/3969630-1.html All Business News: Monster to hold more than 275 job fairs Nationwide in 2007. Company joins forces with National Career Fairs<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and produced 12 job fairs its first year. The number of events increased to 275 job fairs in 76 cities in 2007, and increased to over 350 events in 2008.<ref>[http://www.nationalcareerfairs.com/career_fairs/ National Career Fairs Calendar.<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The company has 20 employees.
