{{Infobox recurring event |name = Ohio Renaissance Festival |image = Ohio Renaissance Festival 2.jpg |alt = |caption = Ohio Renaissance Festival in 2014 |location = [[Harveysburg, Ohio|Harveysburg]], [[Ohio]] |genre = Renaissance fair |first = 1990 |dates = August - October |attendance = 165,000 (average) |area = {{convert|30|acre|m2}} |free_label = Stages |free_text = 12 |website = {{url|http://www.renfestival.com/}} }} The '''Ohio Renaissance Festival''' is an annual event that takes place on weekends from late August through October.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hunter|first1=David|title=Day Trips from Cincinnati: Getaways Less than Two Hours Away|date=2003|publisher=Globe Pequot|isbn=0762727497|pages=256|edition=7th}}</ref> This [[Renaissance festival]] is held at a permanent site located near [[Harveysburg, Ohio|Harveysburg]] in [[Warren County, Ohio]]. It was voted Best Festival in Warren County in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kochersperger|first1=Bridget|title=Fall Festivals in Warren County Draw a Crowd with Apple Pies, Sauerkraut and Turkey Legs|url=http://www.ohioslargestplayground.com/about/media-pr/warren-county-news/fall-festivals-draw-crowds|website=Ohio's Largest Playground|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>
The Ohio Renaissance Festival first opened its gates in 1990 in between [[Harveysburg, Ohio]] and [[I-71]]. Over the 25 years the site has been opened, it has grown into a {{convert|30|acre|m2|adj=on}} permanent village with over 100 shops and 12 outdoor stages. The festival is set in the fictional 16th-century English village of '''"Willy Nilly-on-the-Wash,"''' during the reign of [[Elizabeth I]]. [[Walter Raleigh|Sir Walter Raleigh]], [[Francis Drake|Sir Francis Drake]], [[John Hawkins (naval commander)|Sir John Hawkins]] and [[John Dee]] are a few historical figures that reside in Willy Nilly, along with some not so historical but very much entertaining residents. The festival features costumed performers on stages and in the streets, craft shops selling and demonstrating period themed handcrafted goods and artwork, renaissance themed food, and regularly scheduled comedy, music, and acrobatic shows. Featured shows include Theatre in the Ground, [[jousting]] with the Knights of Valour and Shane Adams (the host of Full Metal Jousting -an American reality television jousting themed show.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bourdeau|first1=Annette|title='Full Metal Jousting' Host Shane Adams: 'It's The Next Extreme Sport'|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/04/full-metal-jousting-host-shane-adams-interview_n_1403449.html|website=Huffington Post|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref>) DaVinci Bros. Comedy Opera, Dirk and Guido: The Swordsmen! and the Kamikaze Fireflies (the duo that were featured on America's Got Talent).
The performing cast including the Queen and her entourage along with representatives from each festival shop make a parade circuit through the fairgrounds once a day.
